  "prompt": "What is the success ratio to get B1/B2 visa?",
  "response": "The success rate for obtaining a B1/B2 visa, which is a non-immigrant visa for temporary business (B1) or tourism/medical treatment (B2) purposes in the United States, can vary substantially depending on several factors. These factors include the applicant's country of origin, their personal circumstances, economic and political conditions, and their ability to demonstrate strong ties to their home country, among others.\n\nWhile there is no official published success ratio for B1/B2 visa applications, the U.S. State Department does release visa issuance and refusal statistics by nationality. Generally, visa approval rates tend to fluctuate between different countries based on the bilateral relations between the U.S. and those countries and the volume of applications processed.\n\nFor the most accurate and current information, you might consider looking at recent reports from the U.S. Department of State or consulting with an immigration attorney who can provide insights based on the latest trends and data applicable to your specific circumstances. Keep in mind that strong documentation and preparation for the visa interview can significantly impact the success of your application.",
